      <section eId="sec_59_A">
        <num>59-A</num>
        <heading>Cider tasting</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Tastings of cider shall be conducted by the licensee or an\nauthorized agent of the licensee. Provided, however, a licensed beer or\ncider wholesaler shall not serve as the authorized agent for another\nentity, nor shall a licensed beer or cider wholesaler be involved in any\nmanner with a cider tasting conducted by another entity.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No more than three samples of cider may be provided to a person in\none calendar day.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No sample may exceed three fluid ounces.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No tasting shall be held during the hours prohibited by the\nprovisions of section one hundred five of this chapter.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Any liability stemming from a right of action resulting from a\ntasting authorized by this section and in accordance with the provisions\nof sections 11-100 and 11-101 of the general obligations law shall\naccrue to the licensee.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_59_A__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No person under the age of twenty-one shall be permitted to serve\na sample or handle an open container of cider.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
